#include <stdio.h>

int main()
{
    char data[10001];
    int length = 0;

    char c;
    while (((c = getchar()) != '\n') && (c != EOF) && length < sizeof(data) - 1)
    {
        if ((c == '0') && (length == 0) )
            continue; // Skiping leading zeros

        data[length] = c;
        length++;
    }
    data[length] = '\0';

    // Condtion1 :  Checking last2 digit is zero or not (%100)
    if ((data[length - 1] != '0' || data[length - 2] != '0'))
        printf("NO\n");

    else
    {
        int sum = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < length; i++)
            if (data[i] >= '0' && data[i] <= '9')
                sum += (data[i] - '0');

    //checking divisble by 3 or not? (%3)
        if (sum % 3 == 0)
            printf("YES\n");
        else
            printf("NO\n");
    }

    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
#include <math.h>

#define MAX_ROWS 1000
#define MAX_COLS 100
FILE *file;
int main(int argc, char *argv[]) {
    int m, n;

    if (argc < 2) {
        // Read input from stdin if no file is provided
        if (scanf("%d %d", &m, &n) != 2) {
            fprintf(stderr, "Error: Invalid input format.\n");
            return 1;
        }
    } else {
        // Read input from a file if a file is provided as a command-line argument
        file = fopen(argv[1], "r");
        if (!file) {
            fprintf(stderr, "Error: Unable to open file.\n");
            return 1;
        }

        if (fscanf(file, "%d %d", &m, &n) != 2) {
            fprintf(stderr, "Error: Invalid input format in the file.\n");
            fclose(file);
            return 1;
        }
    }

    double data[MAX_ROWS][MAX_COLS];


    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (argc < 2) {
                if (scanf("%lf", &data[i][j]) != 1) {
                    fprintf(stderr, "Error: Invalid input data.\n");
                    return 1;
                }
            } else {
                if (fscanf(file, "%lf", &data[i][j]) != 1) {
                    fprintf(stderr, "Error: Invalid input data in the file.\n");
                    fclose(file);
                    return 1;
                }
            }
        }
    }

    // Calculate the Pearson correlation coefficients and find the maximum
    double max_correlation = -100; // Initialize to a value lower than the possible correlation
    int col1 = 0, col2 = 0;

    for (int i = 1; i <= n-1 ; i++) {
        for (int j = i + 1; j <= n; j++) {
            double x_mean = 0.0, y_mean = 0.0;
            double numerator = 0.0, x_denominator = 0.0, y_denominator = 0.0;

            for (int k = 0; k < m; k++) {
                x_mean += data[k][i-1];
                y_mean += data[k][j-1];
            }

            x_mean /= m;
            y_mean /= m;

            for (int k = 0; k < m; k++) {
                double x_diff = data[k][i-1] - x_mean;
                double y_diff = data[k][j-1] - y_mean;
                numerator += x_diff * y_diff;
                x_denominator += x_diff * x_diff;
                y_denominator += y_diff * y_diff;
            }

            double correlation = numerator / (sqrt(x_denominator) * sqrt(y_denominator));
            if (correlation > max_correlation) {
                max_correlation = correlation;
                col1 = i;
                col2 = j;
            }
        }
    }

    printf("%d %d %.6lf\n", col1, col2, max_correlation);

    if (argc > 1) {
        fclose(file);
    }

    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h>
#include <string.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

int main() {
    int m, n;
    scanf("%d %d", &m, &n);

    // Allocate memory for the dynamic 2D array
    char ***data = (char ***)malloc(m * sizeof(char **));
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        data[i] = (char **)malloc(n * sizeof(char *));
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            data[i][j] = (char *)malloc(16 * sizeof(char)); // Assuming a maximum string length of 15 characters
        }
    }

    // Read the input data into the dynamic 2D array
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            scanf("%s", data[i][j]);
        }
    }

    // Find the maximum width for each column
    int column_widths[n];
    for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
        column_widths[j] = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            int len = strlen(data[i][j]);
            if (len > column_widths[j]) {
                column_widths[j] = len;
            }
        }
    }

    // Print the properly formatted table with left-aligned columns
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            if (j > 0) {
                // printf("\t");
            }
            printf("%-*s", column_widths[j], data[i][j]);
        }
        printf("\n");
    }

    // Free dynamically allocated memory
    for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
            free(data[i][j]);
        }
        free(data[i]);
    }
    free(data);

    return 0;
}
